# Tag Cloud Implementation Plan

## Goal
Redesign the [tags.html](file:///d:/web%20project/Gallery/pages/tags.html) page to display tags as a "Tag Cloud" where the font size of each tag reflects the number of photos associated with it.

## User Requirement
-   "Tag Cloud" style.
-   More photos = larger size.
-   Reference common web examples.
-   Maintain "rich aesthetics".

## Backend ([scripts/build.js](file:///d:/web%20project/Gallery/scripts/build.js))
-   **No changes required.** The current logic already provides `count` for each tag, which is what we need. Use `data.tags`.

## Frontend Changes

### 1. [pages/tags.html](file:///d:/web%20project/Gallery/pages/tags.html)
-   Modify `#tags-container`. Remove grid classes (`row`, `g-4`) to allow for a free-flowing flex layout.
-   Ensure responsive padding/centering.

### 2. [app.js](file:///d:/web%20project/Gallery/app.js) -> [renderTags()](file:///d:/web%20project/Gallery/app.js#243-273)
-   **Calculate Weights**:
    -   Find `minCount` and `maxCount` in `galleryData.tags`.
    -   Define `minSize` (e.g., 1rem) and `maxSize` (e.g., 3rem).
-   **Render Loop**:
    -   Iterate through sorted tags.
    -   Calculate `fontSize` for each tag.
    -   Render as an inline-block element (e.g., `<a>` tag) with:
        -   Calculated `font-size`.
        -   Pill/Badge styling (rounded corners, padding).
        -   Subtle gradient or glassmorphism effect.
        -   Hover scale animation.
        -   Tooltip/Title showing the exact count: `title="${count} photos"`.

## Styling Strategy (CSS in [app.js](file:///d:/web%20project/Gallery/app.js) or inline)
-   Container: `d-flex flex-wrap justify-content-center align-items-center gap-3 p-4`.
-   Tag Item:
    -   `text-decoration-none`.
    -   `transition: all 0.3s ease`.
    -   Color palette: Use a set of harmonious gradients or a semi-transparent dark theme with accents. Given the dark mode aesthetic, maybe "glass" pills.
    -   Hover: `transform: scale(1.1)`, increase brightness.

## Verification
-   Check [tags.html](file:///d:/web%20project/Gallery/pages/tags.html).
-   Verify widely used tags are significantly larger than rarely used ones.
-   Verify links work (`tag.html?tag=...`).
